Class Filter

    public abstract class Filter
extends java.lang.Object
    abstract Filter implements filter method for all Filters. All other Filter have to extend this Filter.

      • setUpBeforeFilter

        protected java.util.List<VaultEntry> setUpBeforeFilter(java.util.List<VaultEntry> data)
        This method is run before the core filter process starts and CAN be overridden if the specific filter needs to prepare the given entry data to be filtered.

        If other preparations are necessary, which don't affect the given entry data, just return it as it is.

        Parameters:
        data - the given initial entry data
        Returns:
        modified or unmodified entry data

      • tearDownAfterFilter

        protected FilterResult tearDownAfterFilter(FilterResult givenResult)
        This method is run after the core filter process ends and CAN be overridden if the specific filter needs to prepare the FilterResult.

        If other actions after filtering are necessary, which don't affect the given FilterResult , just return it as it is.

        Parameters:
        givenResult - data after the filter process was executed
        Returns:
        modified or unmodified FilterResult
